<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920117-0136</DOCNO><DOCID>920117-0136.</DOCID><HL>   Dividend News:   Ladd Furniture Inc.</HL><DATE>01/17/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8</SO><CO>   LADF</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>DIVIDENDS (DIV)HOME ELECTRONICS, FURNISHINGS, APPLIANCES (HMF)</IN><NS>DIVIDENDS (DIV)EARNINGS PROJECTIONS (ERP)</NS><RE>NORTH CAROLINA (NC)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   LADD FURNITURE Inc., buffeted by sluggish sales in theU.S. furniture industry, suspended its quarterly dividend andsaid it expects to report a fourth-quarter loss of 55 to 60cents a share. In the 1990 fourth quarter, the High Point,N.C., furniture maker and marketer had a loss of $6.7million, or 35 cents a share, on sales of $113.8 million. Thecompany's most recent dividend was three cents a share, paidlast Nov. 15. LADD said it is taking &quot;numerous steps&quot; toreturn to profitability, including cutting staff and costs.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>